revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== {{suffix|en|xenography|ic}} ===Adjective=== {{en-adj|-}} # Of or pertaining to [[xenography]] {{gloss|surgical transplantation between species}}. #: ''The preliminary conclusion was that the SARS virus crossed the '''xenographic''' barrier from palm civet to humans.'' # Of or pertaining to [[xenography]] {{gloss|writing in a language one has not learned}}. #* '''1999''', Roland Marti, ''Abecedaria — a Key to the Original Slavic Alphabet: The Contribution of the Abecedarium Sinaiticum Glagoliticum'': #*: '''Xenographic''' abecedaria are written by ‘non-native writers’ and they are conserved in manuscripts using a script different from that of the abecedarium.
